select
  s.id, 'board', NULL, 'EMS / quality: telesurgery + technology

คำถาม: surgical innovation + emerging technology', '[{"label":"A","text":"Technology not relevant"},{"label":"B","text":"**Surgical innovation + emerging technology**: (1) **Robotic surgery** (current state): - **da Vinci** dominant — multiple procedures (urologic, gynecologic, general, cardiac selected, head + neck) - **Versius (CMR), Hugo (Medtronic), Senhance, Stereotaxis** — emerging competitors - Benefits: enhanced visualization (3D), improved ergonomics, articulating instruments, motion scaling, tremor reduction - Disadvantages: cost, training, no haptic feedback, conversion if equipment failure - Best evidence: urology (prostatectomy), gynecology (hysterectomy); growing in colorectal, hepatobiliary, thoracic, cardiac selected; LACC trial showed lap inferior to open for radical hysterectomy cervical cancer — surprising, prompted reconsideration of MIS for cervical Ca; (2) **Imaging + navigation**: - Indocyanine green (ICG) fluorescence — perfusion, lymph node, biliary, tumor margin - 3D reconstruction + virtual reality pre-op planning - Augmented reality intra-op overlay - Hyperspectral imaging - Cone-beam CT intra-op; (3) **Artificial Intelligence + machine learning**: - Image interpretation (pathology, radiology) — FDA-approved AI for some - Surgical decision support - Predictive analytics (risk, complications, recurrence) - Computer vision (intraoperative — phase recognition, instrument tracking, anatomy identification) - Natural language processing (documentation, charting) - Personalized medicine; (4) **Minimally invasive trends**: - Laparoscopic → robotic - Endoscopic procedures (POEM, ESD, EMR, endoscopic anti-reflux, endoscopic bariatric) - NOTES (Natural Orifice Translumenal Endoscopic Surgery) — niche; - Single-incision laparoscopic (SILS) — niche; (5) **Tissue engineering + regenerative medicine**: - Bioprinting (cartilage, skin, vascular grafts experimental; whole organs distant future) - Stem cell therapy (selected — bone, heart in trials) - Decellularized scaffolds (heart valves, vessels, esophagus, trachea) - Mesenchymal stem cells for fistula (darvadstrocel for Crohn''s perianal); (6) **Diagnostics + biomarkers**: - Liquid biopsy (ctDNA) - Precision oncology - Pharmacogenomics; (7) **Telemedicine + telesurgery**: - Pre + post-op virtual visits - Remote second opinion - Tele-trauma consultation - Telementoring (experienced surgeon guides remote surgery) - Telesurgery (true remote surgery — Lindbergh Operation 2001 NY to France; modern: 5G enables; growing in selected countries); (8) **Surgical training innovation**: - Simulation (low + high fidelity, VR) - Video-based assessment (Coaching + feedback) - Crowdsourced surgical assessment - AI-assisted skill evaluation; (9) **Implants + devices**: - 3D-printed patient-specific - Smart implants (sensors, drug-eluting) - Magnetic devices (LINX, anastomosis) - Bioabsorbable - Wireless monitoring; (10) **Ethical + regulatory considerations**: - FDA regulatory (510k vs PMA pathways) - Learning curve + quality outcomes - Data privacy + cybersecurity - Equity + access (technology gap) - Cost-effectiveness - Informed consent for novel - Conflict of interest disclosure - IDEAL framework for surgical innovation evaluation (Stages 1-5: Idea, Development, Exploration, Assessment, Long-term study)"},{"label":"C","text":"Avoid all new technology"},{"label":"D","text":"Skip safety evaluation"},{"label":"E","text":"No training needed for new tech"}]'::jsonb,
  'B', '**Surgical innovation + emerging technology** — rapid evolution; balance enthusiasm with rigorous evaluation. **Robotic surgery**: - da Vinci dominant; new competitors entering market - Strong evidence in urology (prostatectomy), gynecology (hysterectomy) - Growing in colorectal, hepatobiliary, thoracic - LACC trial NEJM 2018 — surprising: laparoscopic radical hysterectomy for cervical cancer INFERIOR to open for OS + recurrence; prompted reconsideration of MIS in cervical Ca + cautioned ''MIS always better'' assumption - Cost-effectiveness debated for many indications **AI + machine learning in surgery**: - Image interpretation (pathology — Paige.AI, others; radiology — many FDA-cleared) - Surgical decision support, risk prediction - Computer vision intraoperative (phase recognition, instrument tracking, anatomy ID — Cas Squared, Theator, others) - Clinical decision support - Documentation NLP (Nuance DAX, Augmedix) **Imaging adjuncts**: - **ICG fluorescence** — practical, expanding: perfusion (anastomosis, flap), lymph node mapping (sentinel), biliary visualization, tumor margins, parathyroid identification - **Augmented reality** — pre-op planning + intraoperative overlay - **3D printing** — patient-specific implants, anatomical models for planning **Minimally invasive evolution**: - Laparoscopic → robotic for many - Endoscopic procedures expanding (POEM achalasia, ESD early Ca, endoscopic anti-reflux, endoscopic bariatric — sleeve gastroplasty + others) **Tissue engineering**: - Bioprinting still early - Decellularized scaffolds (heart valves, vessels — TAVR + TAVI growing) - Stem cell + regenerative — selected applications (mesenchymal stem cells for Crohn''s fistula — darvadstrocel; others) **Telesurgery**: - Lindbergh Operation 2001 (proof-of-concept) - 5G + low latency enabling near-real-time - Currently telementoring + tele-consultation widespread; true telesurgery limited but growing **Innovation evaluation framework** — IDEAL Collaboration (Stages 1-5: Idea → Development → Exploration → Assessment → Long-term Study) — analog to drug Phase I-IV; structured approach to surgical innovation evaluation; rigorous + safe vs unevaluated adoption. **FDA regulation**: 510(k) clearance (substantial equivalence) vs PMA (premarket approval — higher risk devices); De Novo for novel low/moderate risk; debates about appropriate rigor + post-market surveillance. **Equity + access**: cost + technology gaps concern; rural + LMIC populations may not benefit equally. **Privacy + cybersecurity** — increasingly important with connected devices + data.', NULL,
  'medium', 'procedures', 'review',
  'surgery', 'ems_mgmt', 'procedures', 'adult',
  'IDEAL Collaboration; ACS Innovation; FDA Surgical Devices', 'AI-generated-board-seed', true, 'seeded via Claude Code session (no critique pass)'
from public.mcq_subjects s
where s.name = 'surg_ems_mgmt'
  and s.audience = 'board'
  and not exists (
