select
  s.id, 'board', NULL, 'Integrative: complex multimorbid elderly

คำถาม: octogenarian with multiple cancers + comorbidities', '[{"label":"A","text":"Standard treatment for all"},{"label":"B","text":"**Octogenarian with multimorbidity — individualized integrative care**: (1) **Comprehensive Geriatric Assessment (CGA)**: - Functional (ADL, IADL, gait, balance) - Cognitive (MMSE, MoCA, delirium screen) - Psychological (depression, anxiety) - Social (caregiver, support, financial) - Medical (comorbidity Charlson, polypharmacy STOPP/START) - Nutritional (MNA-SF) - Frailty (Fried, CFS); (2) **Estimated life expectancy** assessment: - General health, comorbidities, function - ePrognosis tools (Lee, Schonberg) - ''Lag time to benefit'' — does intervention''s benefit timeline exceed life expectancy? (e.g., colon cancer screening benefit ~ 10 yr → may not benefit those with limited life expectancy); (3) **Cancer-specific considerations**: - Aggressive vs indolent cancer - Treatment goals: cure vs control vs palliation - Treatment tolerability based on functional reserve - Geriatric oncology (G8, CARG, CRASH tools predict toxicity); (4) **Polypharmacy + deprescribing**: - Beers Criteria — potentially inappropriate medications - STOPP/START - Simplify regimens - Reassess each medication''s continued benefit - Common: anticholinergics (cognition, falls), benzodiazepines (cognition, falls, dependence), opioids (cognition, falls, constipation), NSAIDs (renal, GI), statins (debated in very elderly with limited life expectancy); (5) **Goals of care discussion**: - Patient''s values + preferences - What outcomes matter (function, independence, comfort, time, family) - Trade-offs acceptable - Cultural + family dynamics - Advance care planning; (6) **Function-focused care**: - Maintain/restore function as primary goal - PT, OT, rehabilitation - Home safety + adaptation - Assistive devices - Fall prevention (multi-component intervention reduces falls 25-30% per meta-analysis); (7) **Cognitive impairment management**: - Identify (screening, diagnosis, type — Alzheimer''s, vascular, Lewy body, frontotemporal, mixed) - Cognition + behavioral support - Delirium prevention (HELP, ABCDEF bundles, mobility, sleep, hydration, vision/hearing aids, family presence, restraint avoidance) - Caregiver education + support - Advance care planning while capacity intact; (8) **Multimorbidity management** — chronic disease optimization: - HF, CKD, COPD, DM, AF, etc. - Coordinated care; - Avoid disease-specific guideline-driven care that conflicts (e.g., aspirin for primary prevention controversial in very elderly); (9) **Social + caregiver**: - Caregiver burden assessment - Respite - Community resources - Home health services - Long-term care planning (independent living, assisted, skilled nursing, hospice); (10) **Integrated geriatric care models**: - Geriatric consultation services - Acute Care for Elders (ACE) units - PACE (Programs of All-Inclusive Care for Elderly) - Primary care + geriatric clinics - Geriatric trauma + surgery programs (ACS Geriatric Surgery Verification); (11) **Quality of life > quantity** often preferred by elderly — should drive decisions"},{"label":"C","text":"Avoid all treatment"},{"label":"D","text":"Discharge home without follow-up"},{"label":"E","text":"Same as young adult"}]'::jsonb,
  'B', '**Geriatric surgical / oncologic care** — individualization paramount given heterogeneity of elderly. **Heterogeneity**: chronologic age ≠ biological age. Many 80-yr-olds robust, some 60-yr-olds frail. **Comprehensive Geriatric Assessment (CGA)** — multidimensional; predicts outcomes better than chronological age alone. **Tools**: - Frailty: Fried, Clinical Frailty Scale (CFS — Rockwood), Modified Frailty Index, Edmonton Frail - Cognition: MMSE, MoCA, Mini-Cog, delirium (CAM) - Function: ADL/IADL, gait speed (slow < 0.8 m/s independent risk), grip strength - Comorbidity: Charlson, CIRS-G - Polypharmacy: Beers, STOPP/START - Cancer-specific: G8, CARG (chemo toxicity), CRASH score **Geriatric oncology principles**: - Tumor biology + behavior - Patient''s functional + cognitive reserve - Life expectancy estimation (ePrognosis tools — Lee, Schonberg) - ''Lag time to benefit'' — does intervention''s benefit timeline align with patient''s expected longevity? - Treatment intensity individualization (full, modified, supportive) - Geriatric assessment improves treatment outcomes + patient satisfaction (Mohile et al evidence) **Polypharmacy + deprescribing**: - Beers Criteria — potentially inappropriate medications (PIM) for elderly - STOPP/START — Screening Tool of Older Person''s Prescriptions + Screening Tool to Alert to Right Treatment - Common deprescribing targets: anticholinergics, BZD, opioids, NSAIDs, sliding scale insulin alone, multiple antihypertensives, statin in limited life expectancy + frailty - Reduces falls, cognitive impairment, drug interactions, costs **Delirium prevention** — HELP (Hospital Elder Life Program), ABCDEF bundle, NICE delirium guidelines: orientation, mobilization, hydration, vision/hearing aids, sleep hygiene, minimize anticholinergic + benzodiazepine, family presence, avoid restraints + Foley + restrictive environment. **Goals of care + advance care planning**: ongoing conversations; documented; portable (POLST/MOLST); honor patient''s values. **Function-focused care**: primary aim — maintain/restore function vs disease cure alone. PT, OT, rehab, home safety, assistive devices, fall prevention (multifactorial intervention works). **Models of care**: - ACE (Acute Care for Elders) units — inpatient geriatric model improves outcomes - PACE (Programs of All-Inclusive Care for Elderly) — community-based - Geriatric consult services - Co-management (orthogeriatrics, geriatric trauma) - ACS Geriatric Surgery Verification Program (since 2019) — institutional standards.', NULL,
  'hard', 'hemato_onco', 'review',
  'surgery', 'integrative', 'hemato_onco', 'elderly',
  'ACS Geriatric Surgery Verification; ASCO Geriatric Oncology; Mohile SG et al. JCO; ePrognosis tools', 'AI-generated-board-seed', true, 'seeded via Claude Code session (no critique pass)'
