select
  s.id, 'board', NULL, 'ชายไทยอายุ 30 ปี เพิ่งฟื้นจากภาวะปลายเท้าที่อับชื้น + DM ใหม่ + แผลที่นิ้วโป้งเท้า 2 เดือน + ตอนนี้ดำคล้ำ

Exam: 2 cm necrotic ulcer + surrounding cellulitis + foot deformity + decreased sensation; bone palpable through ulcer (probe-to-bone positive)
ABI 0.85 (normal); pulse palpable
Lab: WBC 14,400, CRP 120, ESR 88, HbA1c 11.2, glucose 280
MRI foot: osteomyelitis distal phalanx + soft tissue infection

คำถาม: management of diabetic foot infection', '[{"label":"A","text":"Outpatient oral antibiotic only"},{"label":"B","text":"**Diabetic foot ulcer + osteomyelitis — multimodal**: (1) **Hospitalization** for moderate-severe infection; (2) **IV broad-spectrum antibiotic** cover MRSA + gram-negative + anaerobes — vancomycin + cefepime or pip-tazo; tailor per culture (deep tissue or bone biopsy preferred); long course 4-6 weeks for osteomyelitis (IV → oral switch acceptable when stable); (3) **Glycemic control** strict — IV insulin or aggressive sliding scale; target 140-180; (4) **Surgical debridement** + bone resection (toe amputation in this case); send bone for culture + histopathology; (5) **Wound care**: NPWT consider, offloading (total contact cast — gold standard but contraindicated active infection; alternatives: removable cast walker, crutches); (6) **Revascularization assessment**: ABI normal but TBI/PVR for microvascular DM; vascular consult if pulses absent or non-healing; (7) **Diabetes management** comprehensive: nutrition, education, foot care, eye exam, renal monitoring; (8) **Multidisciplinary** team: vascular, podiatry, infectious disease, endocrinology, wound care, nutrition; (9) **Long-term**: prevent recurrence (foot care, footwear, surveillance), high-risk for recurrence + contralateral involvement; (10) **WIfI score** (Wound, Ischemia, foot Infection) — stratifies + guides intervention"},{"label":"C","text":"No intervention"},{"label":"D","text":"Above-knee amputation immediately"},{"label":"E","text":"Antifungal only"}]'::jsonb,
  'B', '**Diabetic foot infection** — major morbidity in DM; affects 15-25% of DM patients in lifetime; 50-70% of non-traumatic amputations are DM-related. **Classification (IDSA/IWGDF)**: - Mild — superficial, < 2 cm cellulitis, no systemic - Moderate — deeper structures involved, larger area, no systemic - Severe — systemic toxicity, severe ischemia **Probe-to-bone test** — positive (palpate bone through ulcer) has high specificity for osteomyelitis (PPV 90%+ in this clinical context). MRI gold standard for diagnosis. **Pathogens**: usually polymicrobial — Staph aureus (incl MRSA), strep, gram-negative (E. coli, Klebsiella, Pseudomonas), anaerobes (Bacteroides). **Treatment**: 1. Hospital admission for moderate-severe + bone involvement 2. IV broad-spectrum antibiotic per IDSA guidelines; cover MRSA in high-risk (vanco, daptomycin, linezolid) + gram-neg + anaerobes; duration: soft tissue 1-2 weeks, osteomyelitis 4-6 weeks (extended in inadequate debridement) 3. Surgical debridement + culture + biopsy 4. Bone resection / amputation as needed (toe → ray → transmetatarsal → BKA → AKA — preserve as much as possible) 5. Glycemic control (insulin commonly) 6. Vascular assessment + revascularization if PAD; arterial inflow critical for healing 7. Wound care: NPWT, offloading, advanced dressings 8. Multidisciplinary diabetic foot team improves outcomes **Charcot foot** — separate entity: neuropathic arthropathy, joint destruction, deformity; mimics infection on imaging; immobilization + offloading; avoid surgery during acute phase. **Prevention**: foot care education, daily inspection, appropriate footwear, regular podiatry, glycemic control, smoking cessation, BP + lipid management.', NULL,
  'medium', 'id', 'review',
  'surgery', 'clinical_decision', 'id', 'adult',
  'IDSA + IWGDF Diabetic Foot Guidelines 2023; ADA Standards of Care; Lipsky BA et al. CID', 'AI-generated-board-seed', true, 'seeded via Claude Code session (no critique pass)'
from public.mcq_subjects s
where s.name = 'surg_clinical_decision'
  and s.audience = 'board'
  and not exists (
    select 1 from public.mcq_questions q
    where q.exam_source = 'AI-generated-board-seed'
