select
  s.id, 'board', NULL, 'หญิงไทยอายุ 50 ปี ครอบครัวประวัติ medullary thyroid carcinoma + pheochromocytoma + parathyroid disease; ตรวจ genetic testing พบ RET proto-oncogene mutation

คำถาม: management of MEN2A', '[{"label":"A","text":"Observation only"},{"label":"B","text":"**MEN2A (Sipple syndrome) — RET proto-oncogene autosomal dominant; multi-system surveillance + intervention**: (1) **Three classic features**: - **Medullary thyroid carcinoma (MTC)** — ~ 100% penetrance; calcitonin-secreting; develops young - **Pheochromocytoma** — 50%; often bilateral - **Primary hyperparathyroidism** — 20-30%; usually multiglandular; (2) **Genetic testing — RET mutation analysis**: - Confirm proband + cascade testing of family - Specific codon mutation predicts MTC age + aggressiveness (ATA risk classification): - Highest risk (MEN2B): codon 918 (M918T) → MTC < 1 yr - High risk: codon 634 → MTC < 5 yr - Moderate risk: other codons → MTC variable timing; (3) **Prophylactic thyroidectomy**: - **MEN2B**: by 1 yr of age (some advocate within 6 months) - **MEN2A high-risk codons**: by 5 yr - **MEN2A moderate-risk codons**: individualized — calcitonin-guided (basal + stimulated) - Total thyroidectomy + central neck dissection if calcitonin elevated or palpable disease; (4) **Pre-thyroidectomy** — RULE OUT PHEOCHROMOCYTOMA first: - Plasma free metanephrines (most sensitive) or 24h urine metanephrines - Imaging if biochemistry abnormal (CT/MRI + MIBG) - Unrecognized pheo → catastrophic hypertensive crisis during anesthesia - α-blockade then β-blockade if pheo + adrenalectomy BEFORE thyroidectomy; (5) **Adrenal surveillance for pheochromocytoma**: - Annual screening from young age (5+) - Bilateral often (cortical-sparing adrenalectomy in selected to preserve adrenal function); (6) **Parathyroid surveillance**: - Annual Ca + PTH from teen years - Parathyroidectomy if symptomatic / meets criteria - Often multi-gland → subtotal vs total parathyroidectomy + autotransplant; (7) **Familial screening + counseling**: cascade testing first-degree relatives; genetic counselor; predictive testing children at appropriate age (typically before age of expected MTC onset based on codon); (8) **Lifelong surveillance**: - Annual calcitonin (post-thyroidectomy — should be undetectable if cured; rising = recurrence) - Annual pheo screen - Annual Ca/PTH - Education re: pheo symptoms; (9) **Recurrent/metastatic MTC**: - Selpercatinib, pralsetinib (selective RET inhibitors — FDA-approved, dramatic responses in RET-altered MTC + lung Ca) - Vandetanib, cabozantinib (older multikinase inhibitors) - External beam RT for unresectable - Palliative + supportive; (10) **MEN2B distinct features**: marfanoid habitus, mucosal neuromas (lips, tongue, intestinal), ganglioneuromatosis (megacolon); MTC very aggressive — prophylactic thyroidectomy in infancy"},{"label":"C","text":"Discharge without follow-up"},{"label":"D","text":"Standard adult care only"},{"label":"E","text":"Refuse genetic counseling"}]'::jsonb,
  'B', '**MEN2 (Multiple Endocrine Neoplasia type 2)** — autosomal dominant; RET proto-oncogene mutation (10q11.2). **MEN2A (Sipple)**: MTC + pheo + HPT. **MEN2B**: MTC + pheo + mucosal neuromas + marfanoid + ganglioneuromatosis (NO parathyroid disease). **Familial MTC**: MTC only. **RET codon-genotype-phenotype correlation** — guides timing of prophylactic thyroidectomy (ATA risk classification): - **MEN2B (codon M918T)**: very high; MTC develops in infancy; prophylactic thyroidectomy by 6-12 mo - **High-risk MEN2A (codon 634)**: high; MTC < 5 yr; thyroidectomy by 5 yr - **Moderate-risk MEN2A**: variable timing; calcitonin-guided; typically thyroidectomy when calcitonin rises or by adolescence **Critical pre-thyroidectomy step**: ALWAYS screen + treat pheochromocytoma BEFORE thyroidectomy (or any surgery) — unrecognized pheo causes catastrophic hypertensive crisis under anesthesia. **Pheochromocytoma in MEN2**: often bilateral; cortical-sparing adrenalectomy (subtotal) considered to preserve adrenal function; rule out pheo before any surgery on these patients lifelong. **Parathyroid in MEN2A**: multi-gland hyperplasia; subtotal (3.5 gland) or total with autotransplant. **Family screening + cascade testing** — essential; predictive genetic testing of children at appropriate developmental age. **Recurrent / metastatic MTC**: - Selpercatinib (Retevmo) — selective RET inhibitor; FDA-approved 2020; dramatic + durable responses (~ 70-80% response rates) - Pralsetinib (Gavreto) — similar - Vandetanib, cabozantinib — older multikinase inhibitors; less specific - External beam RT, palliative - Calcitonin + CEA — surveillance markers **MEN1 (Wermer)** — distinct from MEN2: MENIN gene; 3 P''s — Parathyroid (HPT, most common), Pituitary adenoma, Pancreatic neuroendocrine (gastrinoma, insulinoma, others); also adrenal, foregut carcinoid. Pheochromocytoma NOT a feature of MEN1.', NULL,
  'hard', 'endocrine_metabolic', 'review',
  'surgery', 'clinical_decision', 'endocrine_metabolic', 'adult',
  'ATA MEN2 Guidelines 2015; NCCN Neuroendocrine; Wells SA et al. (Selpercatinib LIBRETTO-001)', 'AI-generated-board-seed', true, 'seeded via Claude Code session (no critique pass)'
from public.mcq_subjects s
where s.name = 'surg_clinical_decision'
