select
  s.id, 'board', NULL, 'Final integrative: complex multimorbid patient + advance care planning

คำถาม: long-term complex patient management', '[{"label":"A","text":"Single specialist alone"},{"label":"B","text":"**Long-term complex multimorbid patient — integrative care principles**: (1) **Patient-centered approach**: - Understand patient as person — values, goals, preferences, family, cultural, spiritual background - ''What matters to you?'' alongside ''What''s the matter with you?'' - Living well with chronic conditions vs disease-by-disease focus; (2) **Care coordination**: - Primary care medical home model - Care manager / patient navigator role - Coordinated multidisciplinary specialty input - Shared electronic health record - Transitions of care (hospital → home → other) protocols; (3) **Polypharmacy review** ongoing: - Beers Criteria, STOPP/START - Deprescribe inappropriate - Simplify regimens - Adherence support; (4) **Address each chronic condition** evidence-based: - Cardiovascular: BP, lipid, antiplatelet, statin - Diabetes: A1c, foot, eye, renal - CKD: progression, dialysis preparation if advanced - HF: GDMT (guideline-directed medical therapy) - COPD: smoking cessation, inhaler, pulm rehab, vaccinations - Mental health: depression, anxiety screening + treatment - Cancer surveillance (age + history-appropriate) - Bone health: DEXA, fall prevention; (5) **Functional assessment + maintenance**: - ADL/IADL - Mobility, balance, fall risk - Cognitive screening (annual for elderly) - Sensory (vision, hearing) - Dental + nutrition; (6) **Preventive care**: - Vaccinations (annual influenza, COVID, pneumococcal, RSV elderly, herpes zoster, Tdap, HPV catch-up) - Cancer screening risk-based - Lifestyle counseling - Substance use screening + treatment; (7) **Advance care planning** as ongoing conversation: - Healthcare proxy designation - Living will / advance directive - POLST / MOLST (Physician Orders for Life-Sustaining Treatment) - Goals of care discussion + documentation - Revisit periodically + when health status changes - Cultural + religious considerations - Family involvement appropriately; (8) **Palliative care integration** — not just end-of-life: - Symptom management - Quality of life focus - Family support - May coexist with disease-modifying treatment - Concurrent care benefits (Temel + others); (9) **Caregiver support**: - Burden assessment - Respite - Education - Mental health - Financial + legal counseling - Community resources; (10) **Equity + access**: - Social determinants of health (housing, food, employment, transportation, social support) - Health literacy - Language access - Cultural humility - Financial support resources - Telemedicine access; (11) **Patient + family education**: - Disease + medication understanding - Self-management skills - Warning signs requiring care - Resources + support groups; (12) **Hospital + transition care**: - Avoid unnecessary hospitalization (e.g., emergency department, observation alternatives) - Care coordination at transitions - Medication reconciliation - Follow-up appointments - Home health services as needed; (13) **End-of-life care**: - Comfort + dignity - Symptom management - Family support - Hospice when appropriate - Bereavement support; (14) **Population health perspective**: chronic disease management programs, registry-based outreach, quality improvement, value-based care models"},{"label":"C","text":"Discharge without follow-up"},{"label":"D","text":"Acute care only"},{"label":"E","text":"Avoid family involvement"}]'::jsonb,
  'B', '**Long-term complex multimorbid patient management** — challenging but central to modern medicine + surgery. Most adults have multiple chronic conditions; care should be integrated + patient-centered. **Key principles**: 1. **Patient-centered**: ''What matters to you?'' (Berwick + others) — alongside ''What''s the matter with you?'' — frames care around patient goals + values 2. **Multimorbidity-focused** vs disease-by-disease — recognize interactions, prioritize, balance, individualize 3. **Geriatric principles**: comprehensive geriatric assessment (CGA), functional + cognitive emphasis, polypharmacy deprescribing, falls prevention, social context 4. **Care coordination**: primary care medical home, care manager, multidisciplinary teams, shared EHR, transitions of care protocols 5. **Patient + family engagement**: education, self-management, shared decision-making 6. **Health equity**: address social determinants (housing, food security, transportation, employment, social support), language access, health literacy, cultural humility 7. **Advance care planning** — ongoing, not single event; revisit with health changes; healthcare proxy, advance directive, POLST/MOLST 8. **Palliative care integration** — concurrent with disease-modifying treatment; not just end-of-life; symptom management + quality of life + family support 9. **Caregiver support** — major modifiable factor; burden assessment, respite, education, mental health, community resources **Specific tools + approaches**: - **5 Ms of geriatric care**: Mind, Mobility, Medications, Multicomplexity, what Matters most - **Comprehensive Geriatric Assessment** - **Deprescribing protocols** (STOPP/START, Beers) - **POLST / MOLST** — actionable medical orders, portable across settings, complement advance directive - **Healthcare proxy designation** **Models of care**: - **Patient-Centered Medical Home (PCMH)** - **Accountable Care Organizations (ACO)** - **PACE (Program of All-Inclusive Care for the Elderly)** — frail elderly in community - **Hospice + palliative care** - **Chronic care management programs** **End-of-life care** — comfort, dignity, symptom management, family support, hospice when appropriate, bereavement support extending 12+ months. **Quality measurement**: patient experience (HCAHPS), patient-reported outcomes (PROMs), functional outcomes, advance care planning completion, caregiver burden, healthcare utilization. **Equity** — recognize disparities; provide language access, health literacy-appropriate education, address SDoH, cultural humility, advocate for policy changes. **Workforce**: interdisciplinary training, primary care + geriatrics + palliative care; nursing, social work, pharmacy, physical/occupational therapy, mental health all critical; team-based care.', NULL,
  'easy', 'procedures', 'review',
  'surgery', 'integrative', 'procedures', 'elderly',
  'Berwick D — Patient-Centered Care; ACS Geriatric Surgery; AAHPM; American Geriatrics Society', 'AI-generated-board-seed', true, 'seeded via Claude Code session (no critique pass)'
from public.mcq_subjects s
where s.name = 'surg_integrative'
  and s.audience = 'board'
  and not exists (
    select 1 from public.mcq_questions q
    where q.exam_source = 'AI-generated-board-seed'
      and q.board_specialty = 'surgery'
      and q.scenario = 'Final integrative: complex multimorbid patient + advance care planning

คำถาม: long-term complex patient management'
  );

