select
  s.id, 'board', NULL, 'Final integrative: telecare + community surgical care

คำถาม: equitable surgical care + value-based care', '[{"label":"A","text":"Single approach for all"},{"label":"B","text":"**Equitable surgical care + value-based care — system-level approach**: (1) **Equity in surgical care — disparities + interventions**: - **Racial/ethnic disparities**: variable surgical access + outcomes documented in many studies - **Socioeconomic disparities**: insurance status, income affect access + outcomes - **Geographic disparities**: rural < urban access; LMIC global gap (Lancet Commission) - **Gender disparities**: women under-recruited for some surgeries (cardiac), differences in pain management - **Age**: under- + over-treatment at extremes - **Sexual orientation/gender identity**: barriers to care, discrimination - **Disability**: physical accommodation, communication barriers - **Mental illness / substance use**: stigma + barriers - **Refugee/immigrant**: language, cultural, documentation, payment barriers; (2) **Interventions for equity**: - **Cultural humility + competency** training - **Language access** (medical interpreters, translated materials) - **Health literacy-appropriate** communication - **Implicit bias** training - **Diverse workforce** representing patient population - **Community engagement + partnerships** - **Patient navigators** for vulnerable populations - **Sliding scale + charity care** programs - **Transportation + housing + food** support during care - **Telemedicine** to extend reach (with digital divide consideration) - **Policy advocacy** for coverage + access; (3) **Value-based care models**: - Shift from volume-based (fee-for-service) to value (outcomes + experience + cost) - **Accountable Care Organizations (ACO)** - **Bundled payments** for episodes of care (joint replacement, cardiac surgery, oncology) - **Population health management** - **Pay-for-performance** incentives - **Patient-reported outcomes (PROs)** integration - **Risk-sharing** arrangements - **Total cost of care** focus; (4) **Quality measurement** — drives improvement: - Mortality + morbidity - Patient-reported outcomes (functional, quality of life) - Patient experience (HCAHPS, surgical patient experience) - Process measures (SCIP, WHO checklist) - Equity metrics (stratified outcomes by demographics) - Cost-effectiveness; (5) **Population health approach**: - Address social determinants - Preventive care emphasis - Chronic disease management - Risk stratification + targeted interventions - Behavioral economics nudges; (6) **Global surgery** (see prior question on Lancet Commission): - 5 billion people lack access to safe surgical care - Bellwether procedures - SAO workforce density - Surgical volume - Catastrophic expenditure protection - Bidirectional partnerships - Capacity building (vs medical tourism / unidirectional aid); (7) **Patient-centered care** — patient as partner in care: - Shared decision-making - Care plans aligned with patient goals - Whole-person care - Family + caregiver inclusion - ''What matters to you?'' approach; (8) **Quality improvement infrastructure**: - Surgical registries (NSQIP, STS, MBSAQIP, etc.) - Internal quality programs - Audit + feedback - Learning health systems - Just culture - Continuous improvement methodology (lean, six sigma, PDSA); (9) **Technology to enhance equity**: - Telemedicine (with attention to digital divide) - Remote monitoring - AI clinical decision support - EHR integration - Patient portals - Health information exchange; (10) **Workforce development**: diverse pipeline, residency training in equity + advocacy + leadership, lifelong learning, wellness; (11) **Healthcare advocacy + policy engagement** — physicians as advocates for patients + system improvement; SDoH, insurance, pharmaceutical pricing, regulation, public health; (12) **Sustainability + climate**: healthcare contributes significantly to greenhouse emissions; sustainable surgery initiatives — reusable instruments where appropriate, energy efficiency, supply chain, waste reduction (Stanford GreenER OR + others)"},{"label":"C","text":"Avoid all systems change"},{"label":"D","text":"Volume-only metric"},{"label":"E","text":"Single specialty focus"}]'::jsonb,
  'B', '**Equitable surgical care + value-based care** — modern imperatives in surgery + medicine. **Health disparities + equity**: substantial documented disparities in surgical care access + outcomes by race, ethnicity, SES, geography, gender, age, disability, sexual/gender minority status. Multiple drivers — system, provider, patient factors. **Interventions for equity** (multi-level): 1. **Workforce**: diverse training, recruitment, mentorship, sponsorship for underrepresented groups 2. **Cultural humility + competence**: ongoing training, recognition of bias 3. **Language + literacy**: interpreters, plain language materials, translated resources 4. **Patient navigators** for vulnerable populations 5. **Telemedicine** with attention to digital divide 6. **SDoH (social determinants of health) integration**: housing, food, transportation, employment - screening + connection to resources 7. **Community engagement + partnerships** 8. **Policy advocacy** **Value-based care** — shift from fee-for-service (volume) to value (outcomes + experience ÷ cost): - **ACO (Accountable Care Organizations)** - **Bundled payments** for episodes (e.g., CJR — Comprehensive Care for Joint Replacement, BPCI — Bundled Payments for Care Improvement, OCM — Oncology Care Model) - **Pay-for-performance** - **MIPS** (Merit-based Incentive Payment System) - **Total cost of care** focus - **Risk-sharing** arrangements (upside + downside) **Quality measurement** — drives improvement: - **Outcome measures**: mortality, complications, readmission, PROs - **Process measures**: SCIP, antibiotic timing, VTE prophylaxis - **Patient experience**: HCAHPS, surgery-specific - **Equity metrics**: stratified analysis - **Cost-effectiveness**: ICER, quality-adjusted life years (QALY) **Patient-reported outcomes (PROs)** — increasingly central: - Quality of life - Functional outcomes - Symptom burden - Satisfaction - Standardized tools (PROMIS, ePRO platforms) **Global surgery + Lancet Commission** (Meara 2015): - 5 billion lack access to safe surgical care - 143 million additional procedures needed annually - Surgery essential to UHC - Bellwether procedures (cesarean, laparotomy, open fracture) - SAO workforce density indicator - Catastrophic expenditure protection **Sustainability + climate** — healthcare ~ 5-10% of greenhouse emissions; OR major contributor; initiatives: - Reusable vs single-use - Energy-efficient OR design - Supply chain optimization - Anesthetic gas selection (desflurane high GWP — minimize; sevoflurane lower; TIVA alternative) - Recycling + waste reduction - Telemedicine reduces travel emissions Stanford GreenER OR + other institutional initiatives demonstrating feasibility + cost savings + environmental benefit. **Physician advocacy** — professional responsibility to advocate for patients + system improvement; SDoH, insurance reform, pharmaceutical pricing, regulation, public health, climate.', NULL,
